description: Always require confirmation on destructive actions
globs: backend/app/views/**/*.erb
alwaysApply: false
---

# Destructive Action Confirmation

Always add a user confirmation before any destructive action (deletion, release, etc.).

## button_to with method: :delete

```erb
<%= button_to "Delete", path, method: :delete, form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "Clear confirmation message." } }, class: "..." %>
```

## link_to with turbo_method: :delete

```erb
<%= link_to "Delete", path, data: { turbo_method: :delete, turbo_confirm: "Clear confirmation message." }, class: "..." %>
```

## f.submit for destructive actions

```erb
<%= f.submit "Reject", data: { turbo_confirm: "Reject this proof?" }, class: "..." %>
```

## Rules

- Explicit message: describe what will be deleted or the effect of the action
- Do not forget `turbo_confirm` on forms generated by `button_to`
- Exception: logout can remain without confirmation
